Description: Fragment of foot of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel (bowl?). Tall ring foot, slightly flaring and modelled outside. Wholly glazed save for groove at join of foot and floor under. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 594)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 675, no. 342)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1857)
